  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We used cell2location (v.0.1.3) 20 to estimate cell-type fractions at Visium locations, with the aforementioned breast cancer atlas as the reference.",
    "For this task we operated on the subset of 313 genes present in the Xenium replicates and subset the Visium dataset and breast cancer atlas to those genes.",
    "We set the default parameters as suggested in the cell2location tutorial (https://cell2location.readthedocs.io/en/latest/ notebooks/cell2location_tutorial.html).",
    "The analysis can be found at https://github.com/scverse/spatialdata-notebooks/tree/main/note- books/paper_reproducibility.",
    "For visualization, only cell types contributing at least 5% per Visium capture location were taken into account then the quantity at each location was normalized to have a total of 1."
  ],
